 You're absolutely right. This does require some deeper design thinking. I appreciate you bringing this to my attention. Let's rethink our approach to better model the concept of exits and entrances between rooms.

Here's a proposed design:

1. For a one-way exit:
   - The edge from Room1 to Room2 will have Source Properties: {"relationType": "exit", "direction": "north"}
   - The same edge will have Target Properties: {"relationType": "deadend"}

2. For bi-directional exits:
   - The edge from Room1 to Room2 will have Source Properties: {"relationType": "exit", "direction": "north"}
   - The edge from Room2 to Room1 will have Source Properties: {"relationType": "exit", "direction": "south"}

Let's update our WorldModel class to implement this design:

<antThinking>We need to update the existing WorldModel class to implement our new design for exits. This is an update to an existing artifact, not a new one.</antThinking>

